  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Galatians 1:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The apostolic blessing is here as elsewhere summed up in the comprehensive words ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "grace and peace",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". These include the lifegiving power of the spirit as well as the assurance of God’s forgiving love in Christ and peace with an accusing conscience. This verse affirms once more the co-operation of the Father with the Son in devising and carrying out the scheme of man’s redemption.",
        "children": []
      },
